xml:id":219,"ref":220},"Alessia Coccato","Coccato","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6641-2820",{"_":222,"when":223,"who":224},"Marta Fogagnolo revised the text encoding, added dimensions, translation and commentary","2022-10-31","#martaf",{"n":107,"url":108,"height":109,"width":110,"desc":111,"surfaceType":112},[227],{"atLeast":228,"atMost":229},15,22,[231,232,233,234,235],"Kaibel, 1890, IG","Korhonen, 2004, IMusCatania","Curtius, Kirchhoff, Roehl, 1877, CIG","Ferrua, 1941, Epigrafica sicula pagana e cristiana","Ferrua, 1989, Note e giunte alle iscrizioni cristiane antiche della Sicilia",[237,238,239,240,241],"Q2SBPG9F","2EUC82DH","533T8HNS","4HR4GXBX","759ZXHKQ",[243,244,245,28,33,246,247,248,249,250,248,251,252,129],"isic001329","epitaph",{"_":5},"strongly altered, grey marble, likely unspecified (identification based on pxrf)","catina","catania","sicilia","sicily","museo civico di catania","ancient greek",[],{"title":255,"body":256,"divs":257,"editions":284,"images":294,"handnote":300},"ISic001329. Epitaph","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">Τίμη\u003C/span>\u003C/span> [καὶ] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">Ποιμ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἑαυτοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ἑα\u003C/span>υτ[οῖς]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">[καὶ]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">το\u003C/span>[ῖς]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἰδίοις\">[ἰδίοις]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐποίησαν\">[ἐποίησαν?]\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">ΤΙΜΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">ΠΟΙΜ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἑαυτοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΕΑ\u003C/span>ΥΤ[...\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">...]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΤΟ\u003C/span>[..\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἰδίοις\">......]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐποίησαν\">[........]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001329_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001329_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001329.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001329-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Kaibel: Τίμη; Ferrua: Τιμη[σίθεος; Korhonen: Τιμή\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 1-2\">lines.1-2: \u003Cspan>Kirchhoff read ΠΟΙΩ which Ferrua (1941) corrected in ΠΟΙΗ (ἐ|ποίη[σε) but a Μ is clearly legible. Later, Ferrua (1989) suggested the supplement Ποιμ[ένιος]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Ferrua: ἑαυτ[ῷ]; Kaibel, Korhonen ἑαυτ[οῖς]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 4-5\">lines.4-5: \u003Cspan>Kaibel: τὸ[ν τόπον] (scil. ἠγόρασαν)]; Ferrua: το[ῖς ἰδίο]|[ις πᾶσιν]; Korhonen: το[ῖς ἰδίοις]|[ἐποίησαν?]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Time and Poim--- made (this) for themselves and their relatives.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Time e Poim--- realizzarono (questo) per loro stessi e per i loro familiari.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The structure of the epitaph is influenced by Latin epigraphy (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">fecit sibi et suis\u003C/span>) and recurs often (but not exclusively) in Christian epitaphs: for this reason, Ferrua believed that the epitaph was Christian. The formula is used to indicate the dedicant, who is not yet dead, but the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζάω\u003C/span> is often omitted (see Korhonen 2004: 88-89). According to Kaibel, followed by LGPN 3A: 429, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Τίμη\u003C/span>, attested in the imperial age also in SEG 31.1327A, is the name of the first deceased, whereas \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Τιμησίθεος\u003C/span> suggested by Ferrua is not attested in that age. The second deceased could have been a \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ποιμήν\u003C/span> or a \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ποιμένιος\u003C/span> (as Ferrua suggested): the latter is attested in Christian age by literary sources. On the names, see Solin 1982: 1030 and 1256.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Kirchhoff 1877 9512 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">508\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1941 243 no.141 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001456\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001456\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 no.443 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 199 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Cursive Μ, Ο in smaller size; lunate epsilon according to Kaibel. The second line is indented.\u003C/p> Lines 1-3  15-22  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[258,261,264,267,270,272,275,278,281],{"id":259,"html":260},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">Τίμη\u003C/span>\u003C/span> [καὶ] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">Ποιμ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἑαυτοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ἑα\u003C/span>υτ[οῖς]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">[καὶ]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">το\u003C/span>[ῖς]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἰδίοις\">[ἰδίοις]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐποίησαν\">[ἐποίησαν?]\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">ΤΙΜΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">ΠΟΙΜ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἑαυτοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΕΑ\u003C/span>ΥΤ[...\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">...]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΤΟ\u003C/span>[..\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἰδίοις\">......]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐποίησαν\">[........]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":262,"html":263},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001329_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001329_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001329.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001329-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":265,"html":266},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Kaibel: Τίμη; Ferrua: Τιμη[σίθεος; Korhonen: Τιμή\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 1-2\">lines.1-2: \u003Cspan>Kirchhoff read ΠΟΙΩ which Ferrua (1941) corrected in ΠΟΙΗ (ἐ|ποίη[σε) but a Μ is clearly legible. Later, Ferrua (1989) suggested the supplement Ποιμ[ένιος]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Ferrua: ἑαυτ[ῷ]; Kaibel, Korhonen ἑαυτ[οῖς]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 4-5\">lines.4-5: \u003Cspan>Kaibel: τὸ[ν τόπον] (scil. ἠγόρασαν)]; Ferrua: το[ῖς ἰδίο]|[ις πᾶσιν]; Korhonen: το[ῖς ἰδίοις]|[ἐποίησαν?]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":268,"html":269},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Time and Poim--- made (this) for themselves and their relatives.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":268,"html":271},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Time e Poim--- realizzarono (questo) per loro stessi e per i loro familiari.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":273,"html":274},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The structure of the epitaph is influenced by Latin epigraphy (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">fecit sibi et suis\u003C/span>) and recurs often (but not exclusively) in Christian epitaphs: for this reason, Ferrua believed that the epitaph was Christian. The formula is used to indicate the dedicant, who is not yet dead, but the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζάω\u003C/span> is often omitted (see Korhonen 2004: 88-89). According to Kaibel, followed by LGPN 3A: 429, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Τίμη\u003C/span>, attested in the imperial age also in SEG 31.1327A, is the name of the first deceased, whereas \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Τιμησίθεος\u003C/span> suggested by Ferrua is not attested in that age. The second deceased could have been a \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ποιμήν\u003C/span> or a \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ποιμένιος\u003C/span> (as Ferrua suggested): the latter is attested in Christian age by literary sources. On the names, see Solin 1982: 1030 and 1256.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":276,"html":277},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Kirchhoff 1877 9512 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">508\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1941 243 no.141 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001456\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001456\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 no.443 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 199 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":279,"html":280},"handnote","\u003Cp>Cursive Μ, Ο in smaller size; lunate epsilon according to Kaibel. The second line is indented.\u003C/p> Lines 1-3  15-22  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  ",{"id":282,"html":283},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[285,287,290,291],{"html":286},"Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo",{"id":288,"lang":129,"html":289},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Τίμη\">Τίμη\u003C/span>\u003C/span> [καὶ] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ποιμ\">Ποιμ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἑαυτοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ἑα\u003C/span>υτ[οῖς]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">[καὶ]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῖς\">\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">το\u003C/span>[ῖς]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἰδίοις\">[ἰδίοις]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐποίησαν\">[ἐποίησαν?]\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":286},{"id":292,"lang":129,"html":293},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"